We can try another clustering technique here which is K-means clustering. you have to be a little bit careful about is that you can get kind of different answers depending on, you know how many times,starting values youâ€™ve tried and how and how often you run it so whenever you, when you start k-means it has to chose a starting point for where the cluster centers are often it will just chose, most algorithms will chose a random starting point. So if you chose a random starting point you may get to a solution that is suboptimal. So if you chose a different starting point you may get to an even better solution.
